  "src/templates/python/.pre-commit-config.yaml.ejs": "default_install_hook_types: [pre-commit, pre-push]\nrepos:\n  - repo: local\n    hooks:\n      # Tier 1 — pre-commit local checks\n      - id: lint\n        name: lint\n        entry: make lint\n        language: system\n        pass_filenames: false\n        stages: [pre-commit]\n      - id: format\n        name: format\n        entry: make format\n        language: system\n        pass_filenames: false\n        stages: [pre-commit]\n      - id: typecheck\n        name: typecheck\n        entry: make typecheck\n        language: system\n        pass_filenames: false\n        stages: [pre-commit]\n        # If slow, remove this hook and rely on make check instead.\n      # Tier 2 — pre-push safety net\n      - id: check\n        name: check (tests + coverage + deadcode + CRAP + audit)\n        entry: make check\n        language: system\n        pass_filenames: false\n        stages: [pre-push]\n  - repo: https://github.com/gitleaks/gitleaks\n    rev: v8.18.0\n    hooks:\n      - id: gitleaks\n        stages: [pre-commit]\n",
  "src/templates/python/AGENTS.md.ejs": "# Agent Instructions\n\n## Validation\n\n- `make lint` — run often during development\n- `make check` — run before considering work done\n- `make quality` — run before marking work complete\n- Prefer `nix develop path:. --command make check` so required tools come from `flake.nix`\n\n## Code Conventions\n\n- Reference `src/seed/` for file organization patterns\n- Prefer stdlib; consider established libraries for complex problems\n- Every function that can fail must raise a typed exception\n- No dead code — remove unused code during normal cleanup\n- Aim for high branch coverage\n\n## Testing\n\n- Every source file needs a test file\n- Test error paths, not just happy paths\n- Tests must contain real assertions\n- Use names like `test_should_do_x_when_y`\n- Mock at boundaries, not internal helpers\n\n## What Lint Catches Automatically\n\nDo not worry about these — lint will catch them:\n- File organization\n- File/function length limits\n- Placeholder comments\n- `print()` statements\n- Import ordering and formatting\n",
  "src/templates/python/flake.nix.ejs": "{\n  description = \"<%= projectName %> Python development environment\";\n\n  inputs.nixpkgs.url = \"github:NixOS/nixpkgs/nixpkgs-unstable\";\n\n  outputs = { nixpkgs, ... }:\n    let\n      systems = [\n        \"x86_64-linux\"\n        \"aarch64-linux\"\n        \"x86_64-darwin\"\n        \"aarch64-darwin\"\n      ];\n      forAllSystems = nixpkgs.lib.genAttrs systems;\n      pkgsFor = system: import nixpkgs { inherit system; };\n    in\n    {\n      devShells = forAllSystems (system:\n        let\n          pkgs = pkgsFor system;\n        in\n        {\n          default = pkgs.mkShell {\n            packages = [\n              pkgs.python311\n              pkgs.uv\n              pkgs.gnumake\n              pkgs.git\n              pkgs.gitleaks\n              pkgs.pre-commit\n            ];\n\n            shellHook = ''\n              export UV_PYTHON_PREFERENCE=only-system\n            '';\n          };\n        });\n    };\n}\n",
  "src/templates/python/Makefile.ejs": "COVERAGE_THRESHOLD ?= 80\nPY_DEV ?= --extra dev\n\n.PHONY: lint format typecheck security test coverage deadcode crap audit mutate quality check fix\n\n# Tier 1 — pre-commit hook\nlint: ## Run all linters (Ruff built-in + Flake8 custom ANV rules)\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) ruff check .\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) --with-editable tools/flake8-plugin flake8 --select=ANV src tests\n\nformat: ## Check formatting\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) ruff format --check .\n\ntypecheck: ## Run type checker\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) mypy src\n\nsecurity: ## Run gitleaks secret scan\n\tgitleaks detect --source . --no-git\n\n# Tier 2 — pre-push hook\ntest: ## Run tests\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) pytest\n\ncoverage: ## Run tests + enforce coverage thresholds\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) pytest --cov=src --cov-fail-under=$(COVERAGE_THRESHOLD)\n\ndeadcode: ## Detect unused code\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) vulture src\n\ncrap: ## Compute CRAP scores\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) pytest --crap\n\naudit: ## Audit dependencies for vulnerabilities\n\tuv export --extra dev --format requirements-txt --no-hashes | uv run $(PY_DEV) pip-audit --progress-spinner off --skip-editable -r /dev/stdin\n\n# Tier 3 — on-demand\nmutate: ## Run mutation testing\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) mutmut run\n\nquality: check mutate ## Run ALL checks (tier 1 + 2 + 3)\n\n# Convenience\ncheck: lint format typecheck security test coverage deadcode crap audit ## Run tier 1 + tier 2\n\nfix: ## Auto-fix lint + format issues\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) ruff check --fix .\n\tuv run $(PY_DEV) ruff format .\n",
  "src/templates/python/pyproject.toml.ejs": "[build-system]\nrequires = [\"setuptools>=69\", \"wheel\"]\nbuild-backend = \"setuptools.build_meta\"\n\n[project]\nname = \"<%= projectName %>\"\nversion = \"0.1.0\"\nrequires-python = \">=3.11\"\n\n[project.optional-dependencies]\ndev = [\n    \"ruff>=0.8\",\n    \"flake8>=7.0\",\n    \"mypy>=1.13\",\n    \"pytest>=8.0\",\n    \"pytest-cov>=6.0\",\n    \"vulture>=2.13\",\n    \"mutmut>=3.0\",\n    \"pytest-crap>=0.2\",\n    \"pip-audit>=2.7\",\n]\n\n[tool.setuptools.packages.find]\nwhere = [\"src\"]\n\n[tool.ruff]\ntarget-version = \"py311\"\nline-length = 88\nexclude = [\"tools/flake8-plugin\"]\n\n[tool.ruff.lint]\nselect = [\n    \"E\",\n    \"W\",\n    \"F\",\n    \"I\",\n    \"N\",\n    \"UP\",\n    \"BLE\",\n    \"S\",\n    \"C90\",\n    \"SIM\",\n    \"PIE\",\n    \"PT\",\n    \"PTH\",\n    \"RUF\",\n    \"D\",\n]\n\n[tool.ruff.lint.mccabe]\nmax-complexity = 10\n\n[tool.ruff.lint.pydocstyle]\nconvention = \"numpy\"\n\n[tool.ruff.lint.per-file-ignores]\n\"tests/**/*.py\" = [\"D\", \"S101\"]\n\n[tool.mypy]\nstrict = true\npython_version = \"3.11\"\nwarn_return_any = true\nwarn_unused_configs = true\ndisallow_untyped_defs = true\n\n[tool.pytest.ini_options]\npythonpath = [\"src\"]\ntestpaths = [\"tests\"]\naddopts = \"--strict-markers -v\"\n\n[tool.coverage.run]\nsource = [\"src\"]\nbranch = true\n\n[tool.coverage.report]\nfail_under = 80\nshow_missing = true\n\n[tool.mutmut]\npaths_to_mutate = [\"src\"]\n",
  "src/templates/python/README.md.ejs": "# <%= projectName %>\n\n## Setup\n\n```bash\nnix develop path:.\nuv venv\nuv pip install -e \".[dev]\"\nuv pip install -e tools/flake8-plugin/\npre-commit install\nmake check\n```\n\n## Development\n\n| Command | Description |\n| --- | --- |\n| `make lint` | Run Ruff and custom ANV lint rules |\n| `make format` | Check Ruff formatting |\n| `make typecheck` | Run mypy |\n| `make security` | Scan for secrets |\n| `make test` | Run Python tests |\n| `make coverage` | Run tests with coverage thresholds |\n| `make deadcode` | Detect unused code |\n| `make crap` | Compute CRAP scores |\n| `make audit` | Audit dependencies |\n| `make mutate` | Run mutation testing |\n| `make check` | Run tier 1 and tier 2 validation |\n| `make quality` | Run all validation, including mutation testing |\n| `make fix` | Auto-fix lint and formatting issues |\n\n## Anvil-generated validation gates\n\nAnvil wires validation through the generated `Makefile`. Run `make check`\nbefore handoff or push. Run `make quality` at the final quality boundary when\nyou need the mutation gate too.\n\n`AGENTS.md` gives coding agents repo-local instructions. `.anvil.lock` records\nthe Anvil version, toolchain versions, generated files, and checksums used for\nsafe re-scaffold decisions. Do not edit `.anvil.lock` by hand; rerun `anvil\ninit` or `anvil doctor` instead.\n\nThe seed/reference code demonstrates conventions to follow: module structure,\ntests, typed errors, constants, enums, and structured logging.\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```text\nsrc/                 Source code\nsrc/seed/            seed/reference code and tests\ntests/               Test suite\ntools/flake8-plugin/ Custom ANV lint rules\n```\n\n## Required External Tools\n\nUse `nix develop path:.` to enter the language-specific shell with Python, `uv`,\n`gitleaks`, and `pre-commit` available locally.\n",
